result.execSummary:
The defendant Jose Domingo Martinez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes:
No contact with the victim K.L.R. or the victim's family, and that includes going through social media to contact the victim or her family.
*8/17/2016  The Court advised defendant that he cannot engage in an occupation or participate in a volunteer position that requires him to work or interact primarily and directly with children under 16 years of age.

Cooperate and participate with sex offender evaluation and any recommended  treatment.
*8/17/2016 The Court advised the defendant:   that he is subject to the sex offender registry and must comply with the sex offender reporting requirement; that he may be subject to possible future proceedings  as a Sexually Violent Person under Wisconsin Statutes Chapter 980.
AODA assessment, treatment if needed.  No controled substances or alcohol.   Random urine screens to ensure compliance.

supervisions.notes: On 6/7/2016 defendant was advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms; also advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored.

**MATTER HEARD BY JUDGE CONEN FOR JUDGE DONALD.....
Defendant Jose Domingo Martinez in court with attorney Ann M Heaps.  Defendant Jose Domingo Martinez in custody.  Erin Michelle Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

This matter was originally scheduled for a Final Pretrial Conference today, however the parties have now reached an agreement.

Upon State's motion and pursuant to negotiations, Court ordered Count #1 AMENDED to:  Third Degree Sexual Assault [a Class G FELONY], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 940.225(3), 939.50(3)(g).

Arraignment held.
Defense counsel waived reading of the "Amended Information" and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1 (AMENDED):    Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  

**Upon State's request, Court ordered a PSI with a sex offender evaluation by Dr. Dickey.  NO RECOMMENDATION.

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
